{{!< default}}
{{!-- The tag above means - insert everything in this file into the {body} of the default.hbs template --}}

{{!-- The big featured header --}}
<header class="main-header {{#if @blog.cover_image}}" style="background-image: url({{@blog.cover_image}}){{else}}no-cover{{/if}}">
    <nav class="main-nav overlay clearfix">
        {{#if @blog.logo}}<a class="blog-logo" href="{{@blog.url}}"><img src="{{@blog.logo}}" alt="{{@blog.title}}" /></a>{{/if}}
        {{#if @blog.navigation}}
            <a class="menu-button icon-menu" href="#"><span class="word">Menu</span></a>
        {{/if}}
    </nav>
    <div class="vertical">
        <div class="main-header-content inner">
            <h1 class="page-title">{{@blog.title}}</h1>
            <h2 class="page-description">{{@blog.description}}</h2>
        </div>
    </div>
    <a class="scroll-down icon-arrow-left" href="#content" data-offset="-45"><span class="hidden">Scroll Down</span></a>
</header>

{{!-- The main content area on the homepage --}}
<main id="content" class="content" role="main">
    <article class="post">
        <section class="post-content">
            <p>St. Stephen the First Martyr Orthodox Church is a growing community of Orthodox Christians. Most of us are converts to Orthodoxy. We make our journey in Christ together; in prayer, worship, and fellowship.</p>

            <div id="image_ribbon">
                <img src="/content/images/parish_life/IMG_9749.jpg" />
                <img src="/content/images/parish_life/IMG_2414.jpg" />
                <img src="/content/images/parish_life/IMG_4188.jpg" />
                <img src="/content/images/parish_life/IMG_4245.jpg" />
                <img src="/content/images/parish_life/IMG_9858.jpg" />
                <img src="/content/images/parish_life/IMG_9500.jpg" />
            </div>
            

            <p>St. Stephen's holds services many times a week. Please consult <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/12RZq6anAhaEJgBqe99Ug-3Q1BGVqrEvtFQ5j9tsLC5M/edit?usp=sharing">The Witness</a> for the most up to date and accurate service schedule. Generally our services include:</p>

            <ul>
                <li>Sunday <a href="https://oca.org/orthodoxy/the-orthodox-faith/worship/the-daily-cycles-of-prayer/matins">Matins</a> at 8:30am</li>
                <li>Sunday <a href="https://oca.org/orthodoxy/the-orthodox-faith/worship/the-divine-liturgy/the-divine-liturgy">Divine Liturgy</a> at <a href="#saturday">9:30am</a></li>
                <li>Wednesday Vespers as 6:30pm</li>
                <li>Thursday Divine Liturgy at 7am or 9am (see <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/12RZq6anAhaEJgBqe99Ug-3Q1BGVqrEvtFQ5j9tsLC5M/edit?usp=sharing">The Witness</a>)</li>
                <li>Saturday Great Vespers at <a href="#saturday">6:30pm</a></li>
            </ul>

            <p>We have a Tuesday night Seeker's class as well as special events and small groups. We offer Sunday School each week for the kids & youth.</p>

            <p>Our community welcomes visitors interested in joining us on our journey. If you have any questions, feel free to contact Fr. Joel at weir.joel@gmail.com or (765) 366-8931. Enjoy your visit and may God bless you!</p>

            <p>Our address is 802 Whitlock Ave. Crawfordsville, IN 47933</p>

            <p>
            Keep up to date with <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/12RZq6anAhaEJgBqe99Ug-3Q1BGVqrEvtFQ5j9tsLC5M/edit?usp=sharing">The Witness (weekly newsletter)</a>.
            </p>
        </section>
    </article>
    <article class="post">
        <section class="post-content">

            <p>
            <a name="saturday"></a>
            <h4>Saturday Great Vespers</h4>
            <h5>Weekly. Next occurs {{#thissaturday}}{{/thissaturday}} from 06:30 to 7:15 PM</h5>
            <p>Join us for Vespers; an evening prayer service in preparation for Sunday Liturgy. The service proclaims the "coming of the Light (Christ) into the world". It consists of readings from the psalms, hymns and prayers of teaching, thanksgiving and praise.
            <div title="Add to Calendar" class="addeventatc">
                Add to Calendar
                <span class="start">{{#thissaturday}}{{/thissaturday}} 06:30 PM</span>
                <span class="end">{{#thissaturday}}{{/thissaturday}} 07:15 PM</span>
                <span class="timezone">America/New_York</span>
                <span class="title">Great Vespers</span>
                <span class="description">Vespers is an evening prayer service in preparation for Sunday Liturgy. The service proclaims the "coming of the Light (Christ) into the world". It consists of readings from the psalms, hymns and prayers of teaching, thanksgiving, and praise.</span>
                <span class="location">St. Stephen the First Martyr Orthodox Church, 802 Whitlock Ave. Crawfordsville, IN 47933</span>
                <span class="organizer">Fr. Joel Wier</span>
                <span class="organizer_email">weir.joel@gmail.com</span>
                <span class="all_day_event">false</span>
                <span class="date_format">MM/DD/YYYY</span>
            </div>
            </p>
        </section>
    </article>
    <article class="post">
        <section class="post-content">
            <a name="sunday"></a>
            <h4>Sunday Divine Liturgy</h4>
            <h5>Weekly. Next occurs {{#thissunday}}{{/thissunday}} from 09:30 to 11:15 AM</h5>
            <p>Join us for Divine Liturgy; A Eucharistic gathering consisting of hymns, prayers, a Gospel reading, sermon, and communion, followed by fellowship (which includes a snack, and can sometimes last until very early afternoon).
            <div title="Add to Calendar" class="addeventatc">
                Add to Calendar
                <span class="start">{{#thissunday}}{{/thissunday}} 09:30 AM</span>
                <span class="end">{{#thissunday}}{{/thissunday}} 11:15 AM</span>
                <span class="timezone">America/New_York</span>
                <span class="title">Divine Liturgy</span>
                <span class="description">A Eucharistic gathering consisting of hymns, prayers, a Gospel reading, sermon and communion.</span>
                <span class="location">St. Stephen the First Martyr Orthodox Church, 802 Whitlock Ave. Crawfordsville, IN 47933</span>
                <span class="organizer">Fr. Joel Wier</span>
                <span class="organizer_email">weir.joel@gmail.com</span>
                <span class="all_day_event">false</span>
                <span class="date_format">MM/DD/YYYY</span>
            </div>
            </p>
        </section>
    </article>
    {{!-- The tag below includes the post loop - partials/loop.hbs --}}
    {{> "loop"}}

</main>
